>>How to use RapaNui.

In your project folder, make a folder titled "RN", this is where you will extract/download Rapanui to.
In your main.lua file, put this at the top:


RN = require("RN/localise")
local R = RN
R.init()


In all subsequent files, (scenes etc) put:
	
local R = RN

I hope using locals will make Rapanui perform faster. Functions are now called using (example):

R.Factory.createImage()
    instead of 
RNFactory.createImage()



Project Setup:

PROJECT FOLDER
|--main.lua
|--other assets
|--run.bat or run.sh
|--RN
   |--RNFactory.lua
   |--RNPhysics.lua
   |--Etc